        <summary>Does Wraith work in countries with DPI or VPN restrictions?</summary>
        <div class="faq-body">
          Wraith uses standard WireGuard on UDP, which is fast and modern but is <em>not</em> designed to evade deep-packet-inspection firewalls. If you routinely operate in a jurisdiction that actively blocks VPN traffic, we&rsquo;re open about that and working on obfuscated transports for a future release.
        </div>
      </details>
      <details class="faq-item plausible-event-name=expand_wraith_faq">
        <summary>How fast is Wraith vs. NordVPN or ExpressVPN?</summary>
        <div class="faq-body">
          Wraith runs WireGuard &mdash; the same protocol most modern VPNs use under the hood. Throughput is a function of your distance to the nearest exit and the node&rsquo;s uplink. Our fleet covers EU, US, and Asia, and we continue to add regions. Haven DNS runs on the node itself, so DNS lookups don&rsquo;t make an extra round-trip.
        </div>
      </details>
